Petrel exportfiles (Schlumberger 2016) or comparable corner-point grids provide each coordinate of the eight vertices of a grid cell. As the fundamental basis of all grid-based reservoirs simulators, initially the coordinates of the face and cell centers have to be determined. This can be done in different ways:
The centroids (balance points) of the cells and faces can be used.
As an alternative, initially the face centers of the (up to) six cell faces are determined by calculating the arithmetic mean of its four vertex coordinates: 25xfc=14∑i=14xi,yfc=14∑i=14yi,zfc=14∑i=14zi\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
